Nollywood actress and serial entrepreneur, Didi Ekanem has sounded a note of warning to Africa’s richest man, Aliko Dangote, that she is coming for his position in the near future. In clear terms, the actress wrote on Instagram; “Dangote, I’m coming for you,” after selling out her latest stock of the popular African meal, fufu. In an earlier post, the actress noted; “Dangote sells rice, salt, onions and he is a billionaire. Does it mean that I will become a billionaire tomorrow from selling Fufu? Am I taking a Calculated risk with this fufu business or an Educated guess that I will one day become a billionaire? “See if you run a restaurant and you need me to supply you with clean fufu with no bad smell, send me a Dm now. Fufu is very healthy and should be sold in restaurants across Lagos. My customers @dailymeals_odot are enjoying o… you wey never order food from me before, I hope you can sleep well at night.” Meanwhile, the actress has called on unmarried young women to take advantage of their singlehood to set themselves up financially before other responsibilities begin to set in. Taking to her Instagram Stories, she wrote; “I know how many married women beg me for money daily. Start a business even if na to sell okro and crayfish, sell it and sell it big. No business wey no dey yield profit. Some marriages come with combined efforts financially. So prepare not to lack on your own part. May God equip you all with strength and wisdom to run that business you have been planning since.”